window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>This Christmas, their only way out is together.</b></p> <p>Nora Romano’s day is a train wreck: her ex-boyfriend is marrying her ex-best friend, and a maddeningly attractive man named Cole Danner deliberately derails her biggest work project to save his local skate park.</p> <p>Things get even worse when they both show up at the most Christmas-obsessed house in Arizona, each trying to convince the eccentric homeowner, Marigold Winters, to let them buy the same rare reindeer collectible. Nora and Cole argue. The reindeer ends up ripped in half—and Marigold loses her patience.</p> <p>With a flick of what might actually be Christmas magic, she zaps them into her personal winter wonderland and hands them a list of “festive tasks” they must complete together if they ever want to go home.</p> <p>Now Nora and Cole—two Christmas cynics with matching stubborn streaks—are stuck navigating snowball fights, holiday challenges, and the kind of unexpected spark that definitely wasn’t on the list. And somewhere between the bickering and the mistletoe, Nora realizes the most inconvenient part might be falling for the man she swore she hated.</p> <p><b><i>A Christmas Carol</i></b><b> meets </b><b><i>The Hating Game</i></b><b> in this laugh-out-loud, slow-burn holiday romcom about rivals, redemption, and the very real magic of second chances.</b></p>"; 
